news.title: Pune metro line-III operation may start by year-end
news.para: With two coaches already in place, trial runs are expected to begin in Oct-Nov, following the completion of construction in Sept.

news.title: Indore: IDA unveils plans for commercial-cum-residential building in scheme 136
news.para: "The total built-up area will be 38,600 square metres, with a maximum building height of 60 metres. The estimated cost of the project is Rs 120 crore," IDA CEO RP Ahirwar said.

news.title: Mohali: Deadline for registering plots without NOCs extended
news.para: Online slots for registration had been fully booked, indicating the high demand for this service, due to which the state government took a last-minute decision to push back the deadline.

news.title: Indore administration orders FIR for developing over 11 illegal colonies
news.para: The senior administrative official said that before deciding to lodge an FIR against the colonisers, they were given a chance to present their sides, along with the required documents, in the SDM court.

news.title: Bengaluru: KG Layout site owners demand faster execution of development work
news.para: If the tender notification is any indication, the BDA is expected to complete the asphalting of roads in Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout only after two years. However, given the BDA’s history of seeking extensions for developmental works, there is no assurance that contractors will complete the asphalting within the stipulated 24-month timeframe.

news.title: Court sends bank New India Cooperative Bank' GM, builder to judicial custody
news.para: The accused were to be produced on Friday when their police custody was to end, but EOW sought an extension for further investigation.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat to add six MnTPA cement capacity in Maharashtra & Karnataka
news.para: The company plans to establish a 3.6 MnTPA clinker unit and a 3 MnTPA grinding unit at its existing Belgaum plant, Karnataka coupled with a new greenfield split grinding unit with a capacity of 3 MnTPA in Pune, Maharashtra.

news.title: Kolkata civic body sanctions four small plots
news.para: Mayor Firhad Hakim had asked the department to offer relief to the owners of small plots by relaxing rules so that they can build homes without taking the illegal route of not taking a sanction.

news.title: Jaipur development body earns Rs 15 crore from applications for three schemes
news.para: ​"The civic body has earned Rs 15.23 crore. The response for three residential schemes, Atal Vihar, Govind Vihar and Patel Nagar, was extraordinary. Against merely 716 residential units, the civic body has received 1.52 lakh application forms," said a JDA official.

news.title: Plot holders in Haryana can apply for resolution of enhancement issues until May 14
news.para: A govt spokesperson said the state govt has once again given a golden opportunity to the plot holders to pay a lower amount under the Vivad Se Samadhan Yojana 2024.

news.title: Ghaziabad master plan 2031 awaits Uttar Pradesh government's nod
news.para: In March 2023, it was delayed so that the state's transit-oriented development (TOD) zone could be incorporated into the draft.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh HC issues bailable warrant against Bhopal collector in RERA case
news.para: The petition filed by Pratap Bhanu Singh that RERA had issued an RRC of Rs 23,26,363 in Oct, 2020 with an interest of 10% and the RRC was to be executed by the Bhopal collector.

news.title: Bihar RERA penalises seven promoters for rule violations
news.para: In a first-of-its-kind order, each promoter has been directed to pay the penalty. An official from RERA Bihar confirmed to the TOI that the order was passed by a bench led by RERA Bihar chairman Vivek Kumar Singh.

news.title: Delhi civic body refutes reports of property tax exemption, urges timely payments
news.para: ​In an official statement issued on Friday, the civic body urged residents to disregard misleading information circulating on various social media platforms.

news.title: Tenants in Lagos hit hard as rents double
news.para: With a population of more than 20 million, the country's sprawling, ever-growing economic capital has for years struggled to keep up with housing demand, with some 3,000 people added to its population per day.

news.title: Kerala govt looks to resolve land acquisition deadlock for Bengaluru metro phase-III
news.para: ​​The meeting, involving the Urban Development Department and the Karnataka Industrial Areas Development Board (KIADB), will determine whether Bengaluru Metro Rail Corporation Limited (BMRCL) can proceed with its proposed Multi-Modal Transport Hub in Hebbal.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body seals six hotels for illegal construction
news.para: Among these are Hotel Friends Regency, Hotel Nagpal Regency, Hotel Onn, Hotel Silver Stone, Hotel Diamond and Hotel Surya Regency.

news.title: Gurugram: DLF 1 residents complain about inadequate social infrastructure
news.para: Savita Choudhary, another resident of DLF-1, said, "Water is the major issue in our ward because there is a gap between demand and supply.

news.title: ADB approves $200 million loan to enhance urban infrastructure in Kolkata
news.para: These interventions, which are part of the Kolkata Municipal Corporation Sustainability, Hygiene, and Resilience (Sector) Project, will improve the living conditions and health outcomes, particularly for vulnerable groups including women and children.
